      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Circular Head ¶ Tas. ¶ 10th October 1874 ¶ My dear Sir ¶  ¶ Your letter of 26th Ultimo ¶ Letter not found. ¶  ¶ came safely to hand with the post Office order for £2. ¶  ¶ I propose to go out this wee...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">74.10.10b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Skelton Emmett</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M141, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Circular Head<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Tas.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">10th October 1874</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your letter of 26th Ultimo<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>came safely to hand with the post Office order for £2.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I propose to go out this week for the (supposed) Pittosporum and Agastachys Odorata — I will attend to the drying process by changing the paper daily under Mrs Emmetts care.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With regard to the longer<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Journey I should like to start on the 1st of December or in the event of your coming over whenever the date best suited yourself<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M left Melbourne for Tasmania on 27 January 1875. See M to S. Emmett, 25 December 1874.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— I should be delighted with your company but the fatigue would be great.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>our country is very different to yours —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You can get a horse here without any difficulty — but the track cut by me for the Government when I was sent out in 1859 &amp; 1860 is not now fit for traffach<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>traffic?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— I could however after one or two days labor with a man make it so that you could get 20 miles inland to a large<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">boggy</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>plain, over which the horse could not travel before<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">February</hi>
               </seg>, nor get around without about 3 days labor. — I think however if you come over we could go to the plain and form our<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>encampment 4½<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>miles<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from the Hellyer.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hellyer River. All places named are in the north-eastern part of the Cradle Mountain-Lake<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>St Clair National Park, Tas.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>We could get to the plains the first day. Second day to the Hellyer and find a crossing place,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>3rd day to Rapid river (10 miles) 4th day to the Arthur (7 miles) and on to the Don<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Arthur and Don Rivers.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— so that we could do it in a week — Hargraves the gold discoverer<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>E. H. Hargraves, unsuccessful in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>seeking gold in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Tas in 1864.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>went on it and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to the plains, leaving his horses<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in charge of the servant, and walked to the Hellyer and back to the horses— Hargraves was 48 years old then weighing 20 stone he was greatly fatigued; when I go alone, I manage to reach the Hellyer easily the first day with a weeks provisions in my knapsack fishing at night at the river for Blackfish &amp; Lobster of which the river is full, second day Rapid river and 3rd the Don — a good deal will depend upon the state of the Hellyer — when Mr John Hurst and five other gentlemen went with me to examine the Hellyer for gold,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mr Hurst took a hired servant to be his<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">bodyguard</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>attending to his horse and his own personal comforts — I should recommend your taking a horse all the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>way to the Hellyer, the track could be cleared I think for £3 — and start from thence with a lighter load — I would make my time yours — if it took a fortnight — My oldest son will go with me (25)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If however you change your mind.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>give me instruction accordingly —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mount Ramsay is a [new] name situated 25 miles South of Mount Bischoff<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>tin mine<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and therefore a cold part of the colony — I walked last February from Circular Head to Bischoff and back 206 miles — and enjoyed myself wonderfully well.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You as an old explorer must be quite used to drinking tea out of a tin pannican without milk &amp;c &amp;c<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You can get good accommodation here at £1 a week — my house is too small otherwise I could offer you my hospitality with pleasure — The trip would do you good.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Schooner Melbourne or other traders would bring you over. Piggott Brothers</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">yours sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>S.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B. Emmett</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Agastachys Odorata</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Pittosporum</p>
         </div>
